race.comment: ASPHALT (5) made it five in a row last start when beating a good field over the 1400m last time out. Up to the mile again today, but he is a winner over this trip previously. May need some luck from the draw, but he does have good early speed and he can continue his winning run. FUNCHAL (9) was sound fresh before a strong effort from the back as fave last start over 1800m. Back to the mile today is a bit of a query, though Pike remains in the saddle and she draws a better gate today. Down in weight and can put her best foot forward. ROYAL TORONADO (8) was very strong late in the race behind ASPHALT when beaten 0.5L and will be better suited second-up and out to the mile. He'll be well back from the wide draw, but he carries no weight after the claim of Cooper and he can get over the top of them late. FOREVER BOY (11) has trialled well coming in and can play a leading role on resumption. BE BARDOT (4) won well last time out and has to be included on the back of that performance.
